2007-01-10  Nicolas Maufrais  <e.conti@gmx.net>

	* 0.84.EN
	  - Scott FRASE proof-read 1/4th of the manual. Thanks for the
	    good work, Scott!
	  - Add list of years after copyright on 3rd page.
	  - More "GNU-compliant" GPL notice on 3rd page.
	  - Remove italics in the list of tutorials (node "Tutorials").
	    When using italics in that case, the wiki page does not
	    display correctly (probably a dokuwiki bug)
	* 0.84.FR
	  - Up-to-date with 0.84.EN
	  - Delete a paragraph in node "A propos de ce manuel" which was in
	    double
	  - GPL translated to French (add file gpl_fr.texi) even if only the
	    English version is "official".
	    Having such an important section of a French manual written in
	    English
	    a) cannot be understood by non English speaking people
	    b) is not respectful toward such readers
	    The official English version of the GPL in available in the
	    LICENCE_en file anyway.
	    The translated licence was taken from the GNU website.

